Tom will rent an apartment in a managed building if and only if he is allowed to move in with Fluffy, and the security deposit is no more than $1500. 2000$ is more than $1500.
question_results.question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Tom is allowed to move in an apartment in The Olive Garden with Fluffy.
question_results.combined_program:
set(auto).
assign(max_seconds, 5).
assign(max_mem, 1024).
# Predicates:
AllowedPet(x, y) ::: Pet x is allowed in building y.
ManagedBuilding(x) ::: x is a managed building.
DepositRequired(x) ::: A deposit is required to rent an apartment in building x.
RentAmount(x, y) ::: The monthly rent for building x is y.
DepositAmount(x, y) ::: The security deposit for building x is y.
DepositGreaterThanOneMonthRent(x) ::: The security deposit for building x is more than one month's rent.
DepositEqualToOneMonthRent(x) ::: The security deposit for building x is equal to one month's rent.
Cat(x) ::: x is a cat.
Pet(x) ::: x is a pet.
Owns(x, y) ::: x owns pet y.
Apartment(x) ::: x is an apartment.
Rent(x, y) ::: Person x rents apartment y.
MoveIn(x, y) ::: Person x moves into building y.
Fluffy(x) ::: x is Fluffy.
Tom(x) ::: x is Tom.
OliveGarden(x) ::: x is the Olive Garden.
MoreThan(x, y) ::: x is greater than y.
LessThan(x, y) ::: x is less than y.

# Premises:
ManagedBuilding(oliveGarden).
RentAmount(oliveGarden, 2000).
MoreThan(2000, 1500).
Cat(fluffy).
Fluffy(fluffy).
Tom(tom).
∀x (Cat(x) → Pet(x)).
Owns(tom, fluffy).
∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) → DepositRequired(x)).
# The security deposit for a managed building is either equal to or greater than one month's rent.
∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) → (DepositEqualToOneMonthRent(x) ∨ DepositGreaterThanOneMonthRent(x))).
# There exists a deposit amount for any managed building.
∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) → ∃d (DepositAmount(x, d))).
# Pets (including cats) are allowed in managed buildings.
∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) → AllowedPet(fluffy, x)).
# Tom will rent an apartment in a managed building if and only if he is allowed to move in with Fluffy, and the security deposit is no more than $1500.
∀x ∀y (Rent(tom, y) ↔ (ManagedBuilding(y) ∧ AllowedPet(fluffy, y) ∧ ¬DepositGreaterThan(y, 1500))).
# Deposit is greater than one month's rent if it is more than one month's rent.
∀x (DepositGreaterThanOneMonthRent(x) ↔ MoreThan(DepositAmount(x), RentAmount(x))).
# Deposit is equal to one month's rent if it is not greater than one month's rent.
∀x (DepositEqualToOneMonthRent(x) ↔ ¬DepositGreaterThanOneMonthRent(x)).
# If deposit amount is less than a value, it's not greater than that value.
∀x y (LessThan(DepositAmount(x,y), 1500) → ¬DepositGreaterThan(x, 1500)).
# The security deposit for the Olive Garden is equal to one month's rent.
DepositEqualToOneMonthRent(oliveGarden).
# The security deposit for the Olive Garden is $2000.
DepositAmount(oliveGarden, 2000).
# $2000 is greater than $1500.
MoreThan(2000, 1500).
# Any deposit amount in a managed building must satisfy the constraints.
∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) → (DepositEqualToOneMonthRent(x) ∨ DepositGreaterThanOneMonthRent(x))).

# Conclusion:
AllowedPet(fluffy, oliveGarden)

# Specifically for the Olive Garden, if it's a managed building and has a rent of 2000,
# then its deposit is either 2000 or greater than 2000.
∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) ∧ RentAmount(x, 2000) → ∃y (DepositAmount(x, y) ∧ (y = 2000 ∨ MoreThan(y, 2000)))).

# Tom will rent an apartment in a managed building if and only if:

∀x (Rent(tom, x) ↔ (ManagedBuilding(x) ∧ AllowedPet(fluffy, x) ∧ ∃y (DepositAmount(x, y) ∧ LessThan(y, 1500)))).

# This implies that all conditions for renting are met.
∀x (Rent(tom, x) → MoveIn(tom, x)).
# This also means that if he moves in, he is renting in a managed building.
∀x (MoveIn(tom, x) → Rent(tom, x)).

# Conclusion:
(DepositEqualToOneMonthRent(oliveGarden) ∨ DepositGreaterThanOneMonthRent(oliveGarden))
